Presence of antibiotic resistance genes and mechanisms in ISS 
E. bugandensis
In the 
E. bugandensis
 genomes collected from the ISS, we looked for antibiotic resistance genes using the CARD database [
22
] and calculated sequence identity with the reference databases (Supplementary Table 
1
). We found that these genomes harbour resistance to 23 different multidrug classes, including cephalosporin, cephamycin, fluoroquinolone, and nitroimidazole antibiotics. Notably, a gene from the ACT 
